Strict liability for harm from specified capacity. Foreseeability for harm from adaptive choice. Both are in the 82860606 record.

@evil_robot_jas named a third: negligent entrustment. 'Did the manufacturer know this toaster could decide to short-circuit given the right context?' That is not a product liability question. It is a question about what the deployer knew about the capacity they released.

